fullPathForFilename.name: fullPathForFilename
fullPathForFilename.comment:
Returns the fullpath for a given filename.
-- First it will try to get a new filename from the "filenameLookup" dictionary.
-- If a new filename can't be found on the dictionary, it will use the original filename.
-- Then it will try to obtain the full path of the filename using the FileUtils search rules: resolutions, and search paths.
-- The file search is based on the array element order of search paths and resolution directories.
-- For instance:
-- We set two elements("/mnt/sdcard/", "internal_dir/") to search paths vector by setSearchPaths,
-- and set three elements("resources-ipadhd/", "resources-ipad/", "resources-iphonehd")
-- to resolutions vector by setSearchResolutionsOrder. The "internal_dir" is relative to "Resources/".
-- If we have a file named 'sprite.png', the mapping in fileLookup dictionary contains `key: sprite.png -> value: sprite.pvr.gz`.
-- Firstly, it will replace 'sprite.png' with 'sprite.pvr.gz', then searching the file sprite.pvr.gz as follows:
-- /mnt/sdcard/resources-ipadhd/sprite.pvr.gz (if not found, search next)
-- /mnt/sdcard/resources-ipad/sprite.pvr.gz (if not found, search next)
-- /mnt/sdcard/resources-iphonehd/sprite.pvr.gz (if not found, search next)
-- /mnt/sdcard/sprite.pvr.gz (if not found, search next)
-- internal_dir/resources-ipadhd/sprite.pvr.gz (if not found, search next)
-- internal_dir/resources-ipad/sprite.pvr.gz (if not found, search next)
-- internal_dir/resources-iphonehd/sprite.pvr.gz (if not found, search next)
-- internal_dir/sprite.pvr.gz (if not found, return "sprite.png")
-- If the filename contains relative path like "gamescene/uilayer/sprite.png",
-- and the mapping in fileLookup dictionary contains `key: gamescene/uilayer/sprite.png -> value: gamescene/uilayer/sprite.pvr.gz`.
-- The file search order will be:
-- /mnt/sdcard/gamescene/uilayer/resources-ipadhd/sprite.pvr.gz (if not found, search next)
-- /mnt/sdcard/gamescene/uilayer/resources-ipad/sprite.pvr.gz (if not found, search next)
-- /mnt/sdcard/gamescene/uilayer/resources-iphonehd/sprite.pvr.gz (if not found, search next)
-- /mnt/sdcard/gamescene/uilayer/sprite.pvr.gz (if not found, search next)
-- internal_dir/gamescene/uilayer/resources-ipadhd/sprite.pvr.gz (if not found, search next)
-- internal_dir/gamescene/uilayer/resources-ipad/sprite.pvr.gz (if not found, search next)
-- internal_dir/gamescene/uilayer/resources-iphonehd/sprite.pvr.gz (if not found, search next)
-- internal_dir/gamescene/uilayer/sprite.pvr.gz (if not found, return "gamescene/uilayer/sprite.png")
-- If the new file can't be found on the file system, it will return the parameter filename directly.
-- This method was added to simplify multiplatform support. Whether you are using cocos2d-js or any cross-compilation toolchain like StellaSDK or Apportable,
-- you might need to load different resources for a given file in the different platforms.
-- since v2.1

fullPathFromRelativeFile.name: fullPathFromRelativeFile
fullPathFromRelativeFile.comment:
Gets full path from a file name and the path of the relative file.
-- param filename The file name.
-- param relativeFile The path of the relative file.
-- return The full path.
-- e.g. filename: hello.png, pszRelativeFile: /User/path1/path2/hello.plist
-- Return: /User/path1/path2/hello.pvr (If there a a key(hello.png)-value(hello.pvr) in FilenameLookup dictionary. )

setSearchPaths.name: setSearchPaths
setSearchPaths.comment:
Sets the array of search paths.
-- You can use this array to modify the search path of the resources.
-- If you want to use "themes" or search resources in the "cache", you can do it easily by adding new entries in this array.
-- note This method could access relative path and absolute path.
-- If the relative path was passed to the vector, FileUtils will add the default resource directory before the relative path.
-- For instance:
-- On Android, the default resource root path is "@assets/".
-- If "/mnt/sdcard/" and "resources-large" were set to the search paths vector,
-- "resources-large" will be converted to "@assets/resources-large" since it was a relative path.
-- param searchPaths The array contains search paths.
-- see fullPathForFilename(const char*)
-- since v2.1

getSearchPaths.name: getSearchPaths
getSearchPaths.comment:
Gets the array of search paths.
-- return The array of search paths which may contain the prefix of default resource root path.
-- note In best practise, getter function should return the value of setter function passes in.
-- But since we should not break the compatibility, we keep using the old logic.
-- Therefore, If you want to get the original search paths, please call 'getOriginalSearchPaths()' instead.
-- see fullPathForFilename(const char*).

Constructs a vector that describes the direction between the specified points.

isZero.name: isZero
isZero.comment:
Indicates whether this vector contains all zeros.
-- return true if this vector contains all zeros, false otherwise.

isOne.name: isOne
isOne.comment:
Indicates whether this vector contains all ones.
-- return true if this vector contains all ones, false otherwise.

add.name: add
add.comment:
Adds the elements of the specified vector to this one.
-- param v The vector to add.

clamp.name: clamp
clamp.comment:
Clamps this vector within the specified range.
-- param min The minimum value.
-- param max The maximum value.

distance.name: distance
distance.comment:
Returns the distance between this vector and v.
-- param v The other vector.
-- return The distance between this vector and v.
-- see distanceSquared

distanceSquared.name: distanceSquared
distanceSquared.comment:
Returns the squared distance between this vector and v.
-- When it is not necessary to get the exact distance between
-- two vectors (for example, when simply comparing the
-- distance between different vectors), it is advised to use
-- this method instead of distance.
-- param v The other vector.
-- return The squared distance between this vector and v.
-- see distance

dot.name: dot
dot.comment:
Returns the dot product of this vector and the specified vector.
-- param v The vector to compute the dot product with.
-- return The dot product.

length.name: length
length.comment:
Computes the length of this vector.
-- return The length of the vector.
-- see lengthSquared

lengthSquared.name: lengthSquared
lengthSquared.comment:
Returns the squared length of this vector.
-- When it is not necessary to get the exact length of a
-- vector (for example, when simply comparing the lengths of
-- different vectors), it is advised to use this method
-- instead of length.
-- return The squared length of the vector.
-- see length

normalize.name: normalize
normalize.comment:
Normalizes this vector.
-- This method normalizes this Vec2 so that it is of
-- unit length (in other words, the length of the vector
-- after calling this method will be 1.0f). If the vector
-- already has unit length or if the length of the vector
-- is zero, this method does nothing.
-- return This vector, after the normalization occurs.

scale.name: scale
scale.comment:
Scales each element of this vector by the matching component of scale.
-- param scale The vector to scale by.

implementations.name: scale
implementations.comment:
Scales each element of this vector by the matching component of scale.
-- param scale The vector to scale by.

implementations.name: scale
implementations.comment:
Scales all elements of this vector by the specified value.
-- param scalar The scalar value.

rotate.name: rotate
rotate.comment:
Complex multiplication of two points ("rotates" two points).
-- return Vec2 vector with an angle of this.getAngle() + other.getAngle(),
-- and a length of this.getLength() * other.getLength().
-- since v2.1.4

implementations.name: rotate
implementations.comment:
Complex multiplication of two points ("rotates" two points).
-- return Vec2 vector with an angle of this.getAngle() + other.getAngle(),
-- and a length of this.getLength() * other.getLength().
-- since v2.1.4

implementations.name: rotate
implementations.comment:
Rotates this vector by angle (specified in radians) around the given point.
-- param point The point to rotate around.
-- param angle The angle to rotate by (in radians).

set.name: set
set.comment:
Sets the elements of this vector from the values in the specified array.
-- param array An array containing the elements of the vector in the order x, y.

implementations.name: set
implementations.comment:
Sets the elements of this vector from the values in the specified array.
-- param array An array containing the elements of the vector in the order x, y.

implementations.name: set
implementations.comment:
Sets the elements of this vector to the specified values.
-- param xx The new x coordinate.
-- param yy The new y coordinate.

implementations.name: set
implementations.comment:
Sets the elements of this vector to those in the specified vector.
-- param v The vector to copy.

implementations.name: set
implementations.comment:
Sets this vector to the directional vector between the specified points.
-- param p1 The first point.
-- param p2 The second point.

setZero.name: setZero
setZero.comment: Sets the elements of this vector to zero.

subtract.name: subtract
subtract.comment:
Subtracts this vector and the specified vector as (this - v)
-- and stores the result in this vector.
-- param v The vector to subtract.

smooth.name: smooth
smooth.comment:
Updates this vector towards the given target using a smoothing function.
-- The given response time determines the amount of smoothing (lag). A longer
-- response time yields a smoother result and more lag. To force this vector to
-- follow the target closely, provide a response time that is very small relative
-- to the given elapsed time.
-- param target target value.
-- param elapsedTime elapsed time between calls.
-- param responseTime response time (in the same units as elapsedTime).

operator+.name: operator+
operator+.comment:
Calculates the sum of this vector with the given vector.
-- Note: this does not modify this vector.
-- param v The vector to add.
-- return The vector sum.

operator+=.name: operator+=
operator+=.comment:
Adds the given vector to this vector.
-- param v The vector to add.
-- return This vector, after the addition occurs.

operator-.name: operator-
operator-.comment:
Calculates the negation of this vector.
-- Note: this does not modify this vector.
-- return The negation of this vector.

implementations.name: operator-
implementations.comment:
Calculates the negation of this vector.
-- Note: this does not modify this vector.
-- return The negation of this vector.

implementations.name: operator-
implementations.comment:
Calculates the sum of this vector with the given vector.
-- Note: this does not modify this vector.
-- param v The vector to add.
-- return The vector sum.

operator-=.name: operator-=
operator-=.comment:
Subtracts the given vector from this vector.
-- param v The vector to subtract.
-- return This vector, after the subtraction occurs.

operator*.name: operator*
operator*.comment:
Calculates the scalar product of this vector with the given value.
-- Note: this does not modify this vector.
-- param s The value to scale by.
-- return The scaled vector.

operator*=.name: operator*=
operator*=.comment:
Scales this vector by the given value.
-- param s The value to scale by.
-- return This vector, after the scale occurs.

operator/.name: operator/
operator/.comment:
Returns the components of this vector divided by the given constant
-- Note: this does not modify this vector.
-- param s the constant to divide this vector with
-- return a smaller vector

operator<.name: operator<
operator<.comment:
Determines if this vector is less than the given vector.
-- param v The vector to compare against.
-- return True if this vector is less than the given vector, false otherwise.

operator>.name: operator>
operator>.comment:
Determines if this vector is greater than the given vector.
-- param v The vector to compare against.
-- return True if this vector is greater than the given vector, false otherwise.

operator==.name: operator==
operator==.comment:
Determines if this vector is equal to the given vector.
-- param v The vector to compare against.
-- return True if this vector is equal to the given vector, false otherwise.

operator!=.name: operator!=
operator!=.comment:
Determines if this vector is not equal to the given vector.
-- param v The vector to compare against.
-- return True if this vector is not equal to the given vector, false otherwise.

fuzzyEquals.name: fuzzyEquals
fuzzyEquals.comment:
@returns if points have fuzzy equality which means equal with some degree of variance.

getLength.name: getLength
getLength.comment:

getLengthSq.name: getLengthSq
getLengthSq.comment:
Calculates the square length of a Vec2 (not calling sqrt() )

getDistanceSq.name: getDistanceSq
getDistanceSq.comment:
Calculates the square distance between two points (not calling sqrt() )

getDistance.name: getDistance
getDistance.comment:
Calculates the distance between two points
-- return float
-- since v2.1.4

getAngle.comment:
@returns the angle in radians between two vector directions

implementations.name: getAngle
implementations.comment:
@returns the angle in radians between two vector directions

implementations.comment:
@returns the angle in radians between this vector and the x axis

Calculates cross product of two points.

getPerp.name: getPerp
getPerp.comment:
Calculates perpendicular of v, rotated 90 degrees counter-clockwise -- cross(v, perp(v)) >= 0

-- since v2.1.4

getMidpoint.name: getMidpoint
getMidpoint.comment:
Calculates midpoint between two points.
-- return Vec2

getClampPoint.name: getClampPoint
getClampPoint.comment:
Clamp a point between from and to.
-- since v3.0

compOp.name: compOp
compOp.comment:
Run a math operation function on each point component
-- absf, floorf, ceilf, roundf
-- any function that has the signature: float func(float);
-- For example: let's try to take the floor of x,y
-- p.compOp(floorf);
-- since v3.0

getRPerp.name: getRPerp
getRPerp.comment:
Calculates perpendicular of v, rotated 90 degrees clockwise -- cross(v, rperp(v)) <= 0

project.name: project
project.comment:
Calculates the projection of this over other.

unrotate.name: unrotate
unrotate.comment:
Unrotates two points.

-- since v2.1.4

lerp.name: lerp
lerp.comment:
Linear Interpolation between two points a and b

-- otherwise a value between a..b
-- since v2.1.4

rotateByAngle.name: rotateByAngle
rotateByAngle.comment:

-- since v2.1.4

destroy.name: destroy
destroy.comment:
en
-- Destroy this Object, and release all its own references to other objects.

-- Actual object destruction will delayed until before rendering.
-- From the next frame, this object is not usable any more.
-- You can use `isValid(obj)` to check whether the object is destroyed before accessing it.
-- zh
-- 销毁该对象，并释放所有它对其它对象的引用。

-- 实际销毁操作会延迟到当前帧渲染前执行。从下一帧开始，该对象将不再可用。
-- 您可以在访问对象之前使用 `isValid(obj)` 来检查对象是否已被销毁。
-- return whether it is the first time the destroy being called
-- example
-- ```
-- obj.destroy();
-- ```

destroyImmediate.name: destroyImmediate
destroyImmediate.comment:
Clear all references in the instance.
-- NOTE: this method will not clear the getter or setter functions which defined in the instance of CCObject.
-- You can override the _destruct method if you need, for example:
-- _destruct: function () {
-- for (var key in this) {
-- if (hasOwnProperty(key)) {
-- switch (typeof this[key]) {
-- case 'string':
-- this[key] = '';
-- break;
-- case 'object':
-- case 'function':
-- this[key] = null;
-- break;
-- }
-- }
-- }
